Exploratory Analysis of Municipalities in Brazil that have adopted a Fare Free Public Transport

Thais Pereira

13/05/2023

Abstract

This report analyse data from 65 Brazilian cities that have adopted the full fare exemption on public transport, more popularly known in Brazil as the Tarifa Zero, a term that will be used in this report to refer to this policy. For the selection of cases, three criteria were used: i. The policy was implemented in all transport networks in the city; ii. It is available to all users and; iii. it was not discontinued until December 2022. We intend to present an exploratory analysis of public data about the studied municipalities and characterize them by checking if there is homogeneity in their economic and social characteristics, in addition to comparing them with all others that have not adopted the policy, with the objective to understand the differences and disparities between the two groups of cities, based on Political Science Teories, in order to undertand why this policy was implemented.

Exploratory Analysis

1.Anlise da Teoria do Eleitor Mediano

1 Premissa: Quanto maior a desigualdade, maior a exigncia por servios pblicos e consequente aumento do gasto pblico. Portanto, cidades com tarifa zero devem ser mais desiguais do que cidades sem essa poltica.

Para verificar se essa premissa de fato pode nos ajudar a explicar a tarifa zero, vejamos primeiro o Gini e o Theil-L, ambos so ndices de desigualdade amplamente utilizados, medem o grau de concentrao de renda em determinado grupo e variam de 0 a 1, sendo 0 uma situao de completa igualdade e 1 uma situao de completa desigualdade, nesse caso esto usando dados do censo de 2010.

degree of income concentration in a given group and range from 0 to 1, 0 being a situation of complete equality, and 1 being a situation of complete inequality, in addition both are using data from the 2010 census. The general median of the Gini index in the studied cities is 0.47, while for municipalities without a Zero Tariff it is 0.49. There is only a small difference in the averages. And the same is true for the Theil-L index, where the median in the first group is 0.4, while in the second group it is 0.45, but similarly the municipalities with Tarifa Zero present values that indicate less social inequality. 2 Premissa: Quanto menor a riqueza medida atravs do PIB, maior a demanda por polticas redistributivas. Dessa forma, cidades com tarifa zero dispem de menor PIB per capita do que cidades sem essa poltica.

Para essa anlise fizemos um corte comparando apenas as cidades com at 150 mil reais de PIB per capta, tanto com tarifa zero quanto sem tarifa zero. Isso no significa retirar muitas cidades da base de dados j que 99,45% das cidades sem tarifa zero (e com menos de 300 mil habitantes) esto dentro desse valor de PIB per capita, no caso das cidades com tarifa zero, isso representa 96,4% das cidades, essa foi uma forma de retirar os valores discrepantes da anlise e torn-la mais evidente.
